            <h2>Getting Started</h2>
            <p>Download the files, unzip them with your program of choice, 
                then copy the file <span class="code-quote">robin.css</span> to your css folder
                (normally, <span class="code-quote">public/css</span>).
            </p>
            <p>Next, include the file inside your HTML head like this:
                <pre><code>
&lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; href=&quot;css/robin.css&quot;&gt;
&lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; href=&quot;https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lato:300,400&quot;&gt
                </code></pre>
            </p>
            <p>
                Note that the second line is important, as Robin does not come
                packaged with its default font. You may change it by adding
                your own font and changing 
                <span class="code-quote">$font-primary-type</span> in
                <span class="code-quote">_variables.scss</span>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
